        {
            "title": "Common Pitfalls",
            "content": [
                "<strong>Word Offsetting</strong> Don't forget to offset by a factor of 4 when trying to access a word (i.e. lw $s0, 4($t0) instead of lw $s0, 1($t0)).",
                "<strong>Use Immediate Offsets</strong> Don't use a register as an offset: lw $s0, $s1($t0) is not allowed.",
                "<strong>Infinite Loops</strong> Make sure that the proper condition will be met to branch in a loop.",
                "<strong>Running Into Branches Unintentionally</strong> If you have a branch in your program, make sure to jump over any other branches so that they are not all executed.",
                "<strong>Signed vs Unsigned</strong> MIPS arithmetic instructions are working with signed numbers unless there is a 'u' at the end of the command (addi vs addiu)."
            ]
        },
        {
            "title": "MIPS Registers (that we care about)",
            "content": [
                "<strong>$zero: </strong> Hard-wired to 0",
                "<strong>$v0, $v1:  </strong> Return values from functions",
                "<strong>$a0 - $a3:  </strong> Arguments to functions - not preserved by subprograms",
                "<strong>$t0 - $t9:  </strong> Temporary data, not preserved by subprograms",
                "<strong>$s0 - $s7:  </strong> Saved registers, preserved by subprograms",
                "<strong>$sp:  </strong> Stack Pointer",
                "<strong>$fp:  </strong> Frame Pointer",
                "<strong>$ra:  </strong> Return Address"
            ]
        },
